#. <section class="sutta" id="sn48.45"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn48.45:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 48"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 48"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn48.45:0.2"
msgid "5. Jarāvagga"
msgstr "5. Old Age"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn48.45:0.3"
msgid "45. Paṭhamapubbārāmasutta"
msgstr "45. At the Eastern Monastery (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.45:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn48.45:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati pubbārāme migāramātupāsāde."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in the Eastern Monastery, "
"the stilt longhouse of Migāra’s mother."

msgctxt "sn48.45:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "sn48.45:1.4"
msgid ""
"“katinaṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, indriyānaṃ bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā khīṇāsavo "
"bhikkhu aññaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, how many faculties must a mendicant develop and cultivate so "
"that they can declare enlightenment:"

msgctxt "sn48.45:1.5"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāmī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"‘I understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence”’?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn48.45:2.1"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …"
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

msgctxt "sn48.45:2.2"
msgid ""
"“ekassa kho, bhikkhave, indriyassa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā khīṇāsavo "
"bhikkhu aññaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr ""
"“A mendicant must develop and cultivate one faculty so that they can declare "
"enlightenment."

msgctxt "sn48.45:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāmīti."
msgstr ""

# Punctuation in MS is inadequate here.
msgctxt "sn48.45:2.4"
msgid ""
"Katamassa ekassa paññindriyassa paññavato, bhikkhave, ariyasāvakassa "
"tadanvayā saddhā saṇṭhāti, tadanvayaṃ vīriyaṃ saṇṭhāti, tadanvayā sati "
"saṇṭhāti, tadanvayo samādhi saṇṭhāti."
msgstr ""
"What one? The faculty of wisdom. When a noble disciple has wisdom, the "
"faith, energy, mindfulness, and immersion that follow along with that become "
"stabilized."

msgctxt "sn48.45:2.5"
msgid ""
"Imassa kho, bhikkhave, ekassa indriyassa bhāvitattā bahulīkatattā khīṇāsavo "
"bhikkhu aññaṃ byākaroti:"
msgstr ""
"This is the one faculty that a mendicant must develop and cultivate so that "
"they can declare enlightenment:"

msgctxt "sn48.45:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘I understand: “Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, "
"what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any state of "
"existence”’.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn48.45:2.7"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ."
msgstr ""
